If you can't access the server's .htaccess file, or have no PHP code to work with, this tool will be your best friend to manage redirections on your websites. The redirect script uses the window.location.replace(url) instead of the window.location.href = url to prevent the browser to push the redirector page to the history, so the users are able to hit the back button without creating redirect loops. The script also contains an html redirect code line for JavaScript disabled browsers. It also has a built-in IE hack to pass the http referer. A link rel="canonical" line is added to the script, so search engines will display your destination site instead of the redirector. xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx Page not found · GitHub Pages
